## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo implementation
async function handleQuery(input, tenantId){
  const lang = await detectLanguage(input);
  const translated = await translateToEnglish(input, lang);
  const tenant = await getTenantConfig(tenantId);

  if (!tenant.consent) return denyResponse();

  const grounded = await searchKB(translated, tenant.kbVersion);
  const prompt = buildGuidedPrompt(grounded, translated);

  const response = await callOpenAI(prompt);
  const redacted = await redactPII(response);

  await logInteraction(tenantId, input, redacted);
  await translateResponse(redacted, lang);

  return redacted;
}
```

## End-to-End Data Path

1. User query → Azure Translator (detect + translate)
2. Translated query → Cognitive Search (KB grounding)
3. Grounded query → Azure OpenAI (response generation)
4. Response → Text Analytics (PII redaction)
5. Redacted response → Data Lake (audit log)
6. Final response → User (translated back to native language)

